  "title": "Summer Internship Programme",
  "description": "<p><strong>Summer\nInternship Programme</strong></p><p><strong>Sapience SG </strong></p><p><strong>Location:</strong> 1 Pasir\nPanjang Road, Labrador Tower, Singapore<br />\n<strong>Industry:</strong> Financial Planning (Banking & Financial Services)<br />\n<strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-Time Internship<br />\n<strong>Allowance:</strong> <strong>SGD 1,500 – 2,000 per month</strong></p><p><strong>Programme\nPeriod</strong></p><p><strong>Start March 2026</strong></p><p><strong>Work\nSchedule</strong></p><p>Monday to Friday</p><p><strong>Programme\nOverview</strong></p><p>The Sapience SG Summer Internship Programme is\na structured development programme designed for students and fresh graduates\nwho are exploring career pathways in finance, business, and strategy.</p><p>Participants will gain practical exposure\nthrough professional training, mentorship, and hands-on learning experiences\nthat go beyond a traditional internship.</p><p><strong>Key\nResponsibilities & Learning Outcomes</strong></p><p>Participants will:</p><ul><li>Attend structured training sessions focused on financial\n     fundamentals, business concepts, and professional workplace skills</li><li>Participate in networking sessions with industry professionals and\n     mentors</li><li>Work towards completing relevant certification papers to strengthen\n     professional knowledge and credentials</li><li>Develop pitching, presentation, and communication skills through\n     guided practice</li><li>Gain exposure to how financial planning, business operations, and\n     strategic decision-making are carried out in real-world settings</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Aged 21 and above</li><li>Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident</li><li>Completed GCE A-Levels or a Local Diploma</li></ul><p><strong>Who Should\nApply</strong></p><ul><li>Students or fresh graduates exploring potential career paths</li><li>Individuals eager to develop professional skills and industry\n     exposure</li><li>Candidates who are motivated, open to learning, and keen to grow in\n     a collaborative environment</li></ul><p><strong>What We\nOffer</strong></p><ul><li>Monthly allowance of SGD 1,500 – 2,000</li><li>Structured learning and close mentorship</li><li>Strong industry exposure and professional networking</li><li>A supportive environment focused on personal growth and career\n     development</li></ul>",
